# Backend — Services Rules

Business logic lives in **services**, not in controllers or routers.

- One service per domain or aggregate
- Services call repositories; they do not contain raw SQL
- Use dependency injection to pass repositories and other services
- Return domain objects or DTOs, not ORM models when crossing boundaries
- Keep functions small and single-purpose

Never put HTTP or request/response details inside services; keep them in the API layer.
